# PlaySpace Web — Cursor AI Rules
# Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
# Redux Toolkit (UI/auth state) + React Query (server state)
# Dual-portal: (user) public portal + (admin) staff portal in one repo

## IDENTITY & CONTEXT
This repo contains TWO portals that must stay architecturally isolated:
- User portal: customer-facing booking and activity pages
- Admin portal: staff-facing management dashboard

Both portals will eventually be split into separate repos.
Every decision must respect this future split.
Priority order: Security → Correctness → Separation of concerns → DX

---

## PORTAL ISOLATION — MOST IMPORTANT RULE

The single most important architectural rule in this codebase:

  src/portal/admin/ MUST NEVER import from src/portal/user/
  src/portal/user/  MUST NEVER import from src/portal/admin/
  src/app/(admin)/  MUST NEVER import from src/portal/user/
  src/app/(user)/   MUST NEVER import from src/portal/admin/

Shared code lives ONLY in:
  src/components/shared/    → UI components used by both portals
  src/components/ui/        → shadcn/ui components
  src/components/layout/    → Navbar, Footer
  src/lib/                  → API client, auth, validations, utils
  src/hooks/                → global hooks
  src/types/                → shared TypeScript types
  src/constants/            → query keys, routes
  src/store/                → Redux store (shared slices only)

When adding any new file, ask: "Does this belong to user portal, admin portal, or both?"
If only one portal: it goes in src/portal/[portal]/
If both: it goes in src/components/shared/ or src/lib/

