## FORMS (React Hook Form + Zod)

  - Every form: useForm<z.infer<typeof schema>>({ resolver: zodResolver(schema) })
  - Schema in src/lib/validations/[portal]/[module].validations.ts — never inline in component
  - Error display: FormField + FormMessage from shadcn — never manual
  - Submit: async (values) — always typed, never any
  - Required strings: z.string().min(1, 'Required') — not just z.string()
  - Money: z.number().min(0).multipleOf(0.01) — never free text
  - Never put submit logic in the component — call a mutation hook
  - Dirty form navigation: warn user with ConfirmDialog before navigating away

---

## API LAYER

  - Single axios instance: src/api/client.ts — never create another
  - API functions: src/lib/api/admin/ and src/lib/api/user/ — pure async, no hooks
  - Never call axios directly from a component or hook — always via API function files
  - Error extraction: always use getApiErrorMessage() from src/lib/api/errors.ts
  - Never catch errors in API function files — let React Query's onError handle them
  - Request timeout: 30_000ms on all requests
  - Unwrap API envelope: return response.data.data (the actual payload), not the full envelope

---

## ROUTING & NAVIGATION

  - Route paths: ALWAYS from ROUTES constants in src/constants/routes.ts
    CORRECT:   router.push(ROUTES.ADMIN.SCHEDULING)
    INCORRECT: router.push('/admin/scheduling')
  - Internal links: Next.js <Link> — never <a href>
  - Programmatic navigation: router.push() after mutations, router.replace() for redirects
  - Protected routes: handled in src/middleware.ts — never replicate auth checks in pages
  - Admin routes: ALL protected by middleware checking next-auth staff session
  - User account routes (/my-account): protected by middleware checking legacy user session

---

## SECURITY — NON-NEGOTIABLE

  Token storage:
    - Staff access token: next-auth encrypted session cookie — never localStorage
    - Legacy user token: keep existing pattern (not changing)
    - NEVER store any access token in localStorage, sessionStorage, or Redux state

  Environment variables:
    - All process.env access through src/config/env.ts ONLY
    - NEXT_PUBLIC_ = safe to expose to browser — no secrets ever
    - If it's a secret: no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix, server-side only

  XSS:
    - dangerouslySetInnerHTML: ESLint warning on every use — requires DOMPurify sanitization
    - User-provided URLs in href: validate before rendering — isValidUrl() check
    - External links: always rel="noopener noreferrer"

  Role-based rendering:
    - Use useHasRole() hook — never inline session?.user?.role === 'X' in JSX
    - Role checks in UI are defense-in-depth only — backend enforces authorization
    - Hide elements from unauthorized roles, but don't rely on hiding for security

  Forms:
    - File uploads: validate type and size client-side in FileUpload component before upload
    - Never disable autocomplete globally — only on OTP/security-code fields

