## TAILWIND CSS

  - Utility classes only — no custom CSS unless Tailwind cannot achieve it
  - Custom CSS: styles/globals.css only — no <style> tags in components
  - Inline style: only for values requiring JS calculation (e.g., dynamic widths)
  - Responsive: mobile-first — base classes for mobile, md: tablet, lg: desktop
  - Dark mode: dark: variant on every color — never hardcode dark colors
  - Colors:
      Semantic: bg-background, text-foreground, border (from shadcn theme)
      Brand/accent: Tailwind palette with dark: variants
      Never: arbitrary values like w-[347px] — use standard scale
  - Class merging: always cn() from src/lib/utils — never string concatenation
  - Class order: Prettier Tailwind plugin order — layout → size → spacing → typography → color

---

## ACCESSIBILITY

  - Every interactive element: keyboard accessible (tab + Enter/Space)
  - Every image: meaningful alt or alt="" for decorative
  - Every form input: associated label (htmlFor or wrapped)
  - Every icon-only button: aria-label
  - Never remove :focus-visible outline — restyle only
  - Color: never as sole conveyor of meaning — pair with text or icon
  - Modals: use shadcn Dialog (handles focus trap + aria-modal)
  - Tables: proper <table>, <thead>, <th scope> — never div-based tables

---

## ERROR HANDLING & UX

  Loading: layout-matched skeletons — never generic spinners for full-page loads
  Errors: ErrorState with retry button — never blank screen
  Empty: EmptyState with CTA — never empty table with just headers
  Mutations: toast on error via React Query onError — never show raw API error
  Forms: inline error messages — not just toasts
  Network offline: useNetworkStatus hook → show banner
  Toast config: success 3s, error 5s — react-hot-toast from root layout

