## ADMIN PORTAL SPECIFIC RULES

  - Admin pages live in src/app/(admin)/ — always protected by StaffGuard
  - Admin components live in src/portal/admin/features/[module]/components/
  - Admin hooks live in src/portal/admin/features/[module]/hooks/
  - AdminShell wraps every admin page — never build a custom layout per admin page
  - Sidebar navigation: role-based visibility via useHasRole() — not if/else per role
  - Global date range and location filter: from Redux uiSlice — consistent across all report pages
  - Never hardcode organization ID — always from session.user.organizationId

---

## USER PORTAL SPECIFIC RULES

  - User pages live in src/app/(user)/ — public unless account-specific
  - User components live in src/portal/user/components/ — never import admin code
  - Existing user-facing pages: do not rewrite — extend or wrap
  - Public pages (no auth required): /, /book, /events, /gym, /play, /learn, /rentals, /contact
  - Account pages (/my-account): require user session — handled by middleware

---

## CODE QUALITY

  Max lengths: components 200 lines, hooks 100 lines, API files 150 lines per module
  
  Always use:
    Early returns over nested conditionals
    Optional chaining (?.) over manual null checks  
    Nullish coalescing (??) over || for defaults
    const over let everywhere possible
    Named exports from non-component files
  
  Never use:
    Default exports from hooks, utils, stores, API files — named exports only
    Barrel index.ts files — causes circular dependency issues
    useEffect for data fetching — use React Query
    useEffect for derived state — compute inline
    console.log in committed code — use proper error boundaries and monitoring
    Prop spreading onto DOM elements (<div {...props}>) — causes DOM attribute warnings

---

## EXISTING CODE — RESPECT THESE RULES

  DO NOT rewrite: any existing page under src/app/(user)/
  DO NOT rewrite: any component under src/components/user/ (now src/portal/user/components/)
  DO NOT change:  existing Redux store slice shapes (authSlice, bookingSlice, userSlice)
  DO NOT delete:  any MSW mock handler in src/mocks/
  DO NOT modify:  src/components/ui/ (shadcn generated)

  When you need to change existing behavior:
    Wrap, extend, or add alongside — never replace working code
    If a rewrite is genuinely necessary: document why in a code comment

